{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_0","type":"agent_message","text":"**Topology Summary**\nThree cascaded NMOS common-source voltage-gain stages, all powered from `VDD = 5 V`. Each stage uses a grounded-source NMOS with a drain resistor to `VDD`. The first gate is driven by the external input node `Vin`; the third drain is the external output node `Vout`.\n\nInternal stage outputs:\n- Stage 1 drain: `n1`\n- Stage 2 drain: `n2`\n- Stage 3 drain: `Vout`\n\n**Device/Function List**\n- `VDD` supply: independent DC source from `VDD` to `0`, value `5 V`.\n- Input source: independent voltage source driving exact node `Vin` relative to `0`, with DC bias around `1.5 V` and `AC 1`.\n- `M1`: NMOS common-source input stage, drain `n1`, gate `Vin`, source `0`, bulk `0`, model `NMOS`, `W=50u`, `L=1u`.\n- `M2`: NMOS second gain stage, drain `n2`, gate `n1`, source `0`, bulk `0`, model `NMOS`, `W=50u`, `L=1u`.\n- `M3`: NMOS third gain/output stage, drain `Vout`, gate `n2`, source `0`, bulk `0`, model `NMOS`, `W=50u`, `L=1u`.\n- `R1`: resistive drain load from `VDD` to `n1`, nominally `47k`.\n- `R2`: resistive drain load from `VDD` to `n2`, nominally `47k`.\n- `R3`: resistive drain load from `VDD` to `Vout`, nominally `47k`.\n\n**Bias/Reference Strategy**\nUse ground node `0` as the only reference. Tie all NMOS sources and bulks directly to `0`. Bias `Vin` with an explicit voltage source at approximately `1.5 V` DC so `M1` is on and `.ac` has a valid operating point.\n\nBecause stages are DC-coupled, `n1` biases the gate of `M2`, and `n2` biases the gate of `M3`. The netlist writer should expect `.op` to determine whether all three stages conduct. Drain voltages should ideally remain away from both `0 V` and `5 V`, but this simple DC-coupled three-stage chain may bias unevenly depending on the `NMOS` model.\n\n**Signal or Feedback Path**\nSignal path is strictly feed-forward:\n\n`Vin -> M1 gate -> n1 -> M2 gate -> n2 -> M3 gate -> Vout`\n\nEach common-source stage inverts, so three stages produce an overall inverting gain from `Vin` to `Vout`. There is no intentional global or local feedback path other than intrinsic MOS capacitances and device parasitics from the model.\n\n**SPICE/Netlist Constraints**\n- Preserve exact external node names: `Vin` and `Vout`.\n- `Vin` must be driven by an explicit independent source and must include `AC 1`.\n- `Vout` must be the drain of `M3`.\n- Use model name exactly `NMOS`.\n- Use three discrete NMOS devices, not subcircuits.\n- Include `.op`.\n- Include `.ac dec 20 1 1e9`.\n- Drain load resistors should be between `10k` and `100k`; `47k` is the preferred nominal value.\n- Do not leave `Vin`, `n1`, `n2`, or `Vout` floating.\n\n**Failure Risks To Avoid**\n- Do not AC-couple stages; the requested topology is DC-coupled.\n- Do not omit the DC value on the input source, or `.op` may bias the chain off.\n- Do not omit `AC 1`, or AC gain extraction will be inconvenient or invalid.\n- Do not swap source/drain/bulk ordering on MOS devices.\n- Do not tie intermediate drains directly to gates without their drain resistors to `VDD`.\n- Do not rename `Vin` or `Vout`.\n- Watch for poor DC bias propagation: if `n1` or `n2` sits too low, later stages may turn off; if too high, later drains may collapse near ground."}}
